{"id":"martyr","term":"Martyr","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>One who bears witness of the truth, and suffers death in the cause of Christ (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 22:20\">Acts 22:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 2:13\">Rev. 2:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 17:6\">17:6</a>). In this sense Stephen was the first martyr. The Greek word so rendered in all other cases is translated “witness.” (1.) In a court of justice (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 18:16\">Matt. 18:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 26:65\">26:65</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 6:13\">Acts 6:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:58\">7:58</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 10:28\">Heb. 10:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 5:19\">1 Tim. 5:19</a>). (2.) As of one bearing testimony to the truth of what he has seen or known (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 24:48\">Luke 24:48</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 1:8\">Acts 1:8</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 1:22\">22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 1:9\">Rom. 1:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Thessalonians 2:5\">1 Thess. 2:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Thessalonians 2:10\">10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 John 1:2\">1 John 1:2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Acts 22:20","Revelation 2:13","Revelation 17:6","Matthew 18:16","Matthew 26:65","Acts 6:13","Acts 7:58","Hebrews 10:28","1 Timothy 5:19","Luke 24:48","Acts 1:8","Acts 1:22","Romans 1:9","1 Thessalonians 2:5","1 Thessalonians 2:10","1 John 1:2"]}